Three people have been arrested in connection with the death of beautician Elle Edwards. Ms Edwards, 26, was shot at the Lighthouse pub in Wallasey, the Wirral, on December 24 2022. Thomas Waring has been charged with possession of a prohibited weapon and assisting an offender. Merseyside Police said he will appear before Wirral Adult Remand Court on Thursday morning. A man from Heswall and a woman from Tranmere have been arrested and released on bail. Ms Edwards is not believed to have been the intended target. Connor Chapman has been charged with the alleged murder of Ms Edwards; he is due to go on trial in June.